RESULTS: Younger patients had more common involvement of extrathoracic lymph nodes, parotid/salivary gland, and liver, while older patients had more common involvement of non-lymphatic extrathoracic organs such as the eye, heart, muscle, and kidney. The age at diagnosis has consistently increased over the past four decades. The monophasic distribution in men has tended to become biphasic, and the biphasic distribution in women monophasic. Increasing trends were apparent for hypercalcemia and involvement of the gastrointestinal tract, skin, nervous system, muscle, and kidney.
