	abstract = {BACKGROUND: Improved access and treatment are critical to controlling the problem. Molecular diagnostic tests, although available, are not feasible in developing countries. Where available, these tests require state-of-the-art laboratories and are not cheap. One alternative to molecular diagnostics is the use of acute phase protein values. This protein is a protein whose levels will increase or decrease in plasma in response to injury or inflammation.
