CONCLUSIONS: These results indicate that the inflammation in sarcoidosis is associated with NF-kappaB activation. Moreover, the suppression of the activated NF-kappaB response by glucocorticoids seems less successful than the suppression of the sACE activity. Future studies should focus on the clinical relevance of this observation and establish the possible therapeutic consequences of the increased NF-kappaB activation in sarcoidosis.},
