	abstract = {Objective:
To highlight potential pitfalls in diagnosis and management of patients with concomitant gout and septic arthritis.

Methods:
Presentation of two patients with concomitant gout and septic arthritis, the latter caused by Streptococcus agalactiae and Staphylococcus aureus, in one patient each. We also reviewed the English language literature on PubMed for similar cases.

Results:
